---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/Docs.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../../components/docs/CodeBlock.astro';
import Callout from '../../../components/docs/Callout.astro';
import PrevNext from '../../../components/docs/PrevNext.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Installation - Claude Plugin">
  <article class="prose max-w-none">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">Claude Code Plugin Installation</h1>

    <p class="text-xl text-text-secondary mb-8">
      The easiest way to use CodeGraph with Claude Code CLI.
    </p>

    <Callout type="tip" title="Recommended for Claude Code users">
      This installation method provides:
      <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
        <li>Automatic Neo4j management</li>
        <li>Simple slash commands (<code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary">/codegraph:setup</code>, <code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary">/codegraph:index</code>)</li>
        <li>8 powerful graph analysis tools</li>
      </ul>
    </Callout>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">Prerequisites</h2>

    <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4 glass-card p-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-primary/20 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 9l3 3-3 3m5 0h3M5 20h14a2 2 0 002-2V6a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-text-primary font-semibold">Claude Code CLI</h3>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm mt-1">
            The official Claude Code command-line interface.
            <a href="https://claude.ai/code" class="text-primary hover:text-secondary">Install Claude Code</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-start gap-4 glass-card p-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-primary/20 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 12h14M5 12a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h14a2 2 0 012 2v4a2 2 0 01-2 2M5 12a2 2 0 00-2 2v4a2 2 0 002 2h14a2 2 0 002-2v-4a2 2 0 00-2-2m-2-4h.01M17 16h.01" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-text-primary font-semibold">Docker</h3>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm mt-1">
            Required for running the Neo4j database. Ensure Docker is installed and running.
            <a href="https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/" class="text-primary hover:text-secondary">Install Docker</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <Callout type="warning" title="Docker Required">
      Before proceeding, verify Docker is running:
      <div class="mt-2">
        <code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-1 rounded text-primary text-sm">docker info</code>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-2">If you see an error, start Docker Desktop first.</p>
    </Callout>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">Installation</h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Step 1: Add the Plugin Marketplace</h3>

    <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
      Add the Bikach plugin marketplace to Claude Code (only needed once):
    </p>

    <CodeBlock
      code="/plugin marketplace add Bikach/claude-plugins"
      lang="bash"
      title="Claude Code"
    />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Step 2: Install the Plugin</h3>

    <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
      Install the CodeGraph plugin:
    </p>

    <CodeBlock
      code="/plugin install codegraph@Bikach"
      lang="bash"
      title="Claude Code"
    />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Installation Scopes</h3>

    <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
      You can specify where the plugin is installed:
    </p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <th class="py-3 px-4 text-text-primary font-semibold">Scope</th>
            <th class="py-3 px-4 text-text-primary font-semibold">Command</th>
            <th class="py-3 px-4 text-text-primary font-semibold">Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-text-secondary">
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <td class="py-3 px-4"><strong class="text-text-primary">User</strong> (default)</td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4"><code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary text-xs">/plugin install codegraph@Bikach</code></td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4">Available in all your projects</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <td class="py-3 px-4"><strong class="text-text-primary">Project</strong></td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4"><code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary text-xs">/plugin install codegraph@Bikach --scope project</code></td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4">Shared with collaborators</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <td class="py-3 px-4"><strong class="text-text-primary">Local</strong></td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4"><code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary text-xs">/plugin install codegraph@Bikach --scope local</code></td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4">Only for you in this repo</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">Initialize CodeGraph</h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Step 3: Run Setup</h3>

    <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
      Start Neo4j and prepare the database:
    </p>

    <CodeBlock
      code="/codegraph:setup"
      lang="bash"
      title="Claude Code"
    />


    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Step 4: Index Your Project</h3>

    <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
      Navigate to your Kotlin, Java, or TypeScript project and run:
    </p>

    <CodeBlock
      code="/codegraph:index"
      lang="bash"
      title="Claude Code"
    />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Step 5: Verify Installation</h3>

    <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
      Check that everything is working:
    </p>

    <CodeBlock
      code="/codegraph:status"
      lang="bash"
      title="Claude Code"
    />

    <p class="text-text-secondary mt-4">
      You should see Neo4j connection status and graph statistics.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">Available Features</h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Commands</h3>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <th class="py-3 px-4 text-text-primary font-semibold">Command</th>
            <th class="py-3 px-4 text-text-primary font-semibold">Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-text-secondary">
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <td class="py-3 px-4"><code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary">/codegraph:setup</code></td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4">Start Neo4j and prepare the database</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <td class="py-3 px-4"><code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary">/codegraph:index</code></td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4">Index your project into the graph</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <td class="py-3 px-4"><code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary">/codegraph:status</code></td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4">Check Neo4j connection and graph stats</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Graph Tools (8)</h3>

    <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">
      Pre-indexed graph queries for instant code analysis:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-text-secondary space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li><code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary">search_nodes</code> - Search by name or pattern</li>
      <li><code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary">get_callers</code> - Who calls this function?</li>
      <li><code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary">get_callees</code> - What functions are called?</li>
      <li><code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary">get_neighbors</code> - Get dependencies and dependents</li>
      <li><code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary">get_implementations</code> - Find interface implementations</li>
      <li><code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary">get_impact</code> - Analyze modification impact</li>
      <li><code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary">find_path</code> - Find shortest path between nodes</li>
      <li><code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary">get_file_symbols</code> - List all symbols in a file</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">Supported Languages</h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <th class="py-3 px-4 text-text-primary font-semibold">Language</th>
            <th class="py-3 px-4 text-text-primary font-semibold">Status</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-text-secondary">
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <td class="py-3 px-4">Kotlin</td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4"><span class="text-secondary">Available</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <td class="py-3 px-4">Java</td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4"><span class="text-secondary">Available</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-border">
            <td class="py-3 px-4">TypeScript</td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4"><span class="text-secondary">Available</span></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">Troubleshooting</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
      <div class="border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <div class="bg-bg-subtle px-4 py-3 border-b border-border">
          <h3 class="text-text-primary font-semibold">Plugin not recognized</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4">
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-3">
            If Claude Code doesn't recognize CodeGraph commands, verify the plugin is installed:
          </p>
          <CodeBlock
            code="/plugin list"
            lang="bash"
            title="Claude Code"
          />
          <p class="text-text-secondary mt-3">
            You should see <code class="bg-bg-subtle px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-primary">codegraph@Bikach-claude-plugins</code> in the list.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <div class="bg-bg-subtle px-4 py-3 border-b border-border">
          <h3 class="text-text-primary font-semibold">Docker is not running</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4">
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-3">
            If you see "Cannot connect to Docker daemon", ensure Docker Desktop is running:
          </p>
          <CodeBlock
            code="docker info"
            lang="bash"
            title="Terminal"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <div class="bg-bg-subtle px-4 py-3 border-b border-border">
          <h3 class="text-text-primary font-semibold">Neo4j port conflict</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4">
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-3">
            If port 7687 is already in use, stop existing Neo4j instances:
          </p>
          <CodeBlock
            code={`docker ps | grep neo4j
docker stop <container_id>`}
            lang="bash"
            title="Terminal"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <Callout type="warning" title="Need Help?">
      If you're still experiencing issues, check the
      <a href="https://github.com/Bikach/claude-plugins/issues" class="text-attention hover:text-secondary"> GitHub Issues</a>
      or open a new issue with your error logs.
    </Callout>
  </article>

  <PrevNext
    prev={{ title: "Getting Started", href: "/docs/getting-started" }}
    next={{ title: "MCP Standalone", href: "/docs/installation/mcp-standalone" }}
  />
</DocsLayout>
